  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tubaramure: Preventing Malnutrition in Children Under Two</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mother-child units from pregnancy to age 23 months</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tubaramure will target the mother and child as a unit as early as possible during her pregnancy, the mother will enter the program and continue in it until the child celebrates his/her second birthday, to achieve the objective of preventing malnutrition in children under 2.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women and Children 0-59 months access quality nutrition and health services. Tubaramure will strengthen the capacity of health facilities and Community Health Workers to deliver high quality general health and nutrition services. The project will work with both governmental and non-governmental health services to advance pre- and post-natal services &#x2013; including Integrated Management of Childhood Illnesses (IMCI), growth monitoring and Community-based Management of Acute Malnutrition (CMAM) &#x2013; and to break the barriers to access; Households practice appropriate health and nutrition behaviors. Tubaramure will promote household and community-level behaviors that prevent maternal and childhood illnesses and support good nutrition. Using Care Groups as the delivery mechanism, the project will promote the uptake of Essential Nutrition Actions and Essential Hygiene Actions, and household-level prevention and management of child illnesses. A well-researched behavior change communication (BCC) strategy will define the specific behaviors to be addressed; Eligible women and children have increased intake of nutrient-rich, diverse foods. Tubaramure will improve the caloric and nutrient intake of mothers and children under 2. The value and use of local foods will be promoted through culinary demonstrations that combine Title II commodities with local nutrient-rich foods.</narrative>
  </description>
